sorcer.core.context.model.par

Class ParModel<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Dictionary<K,V>
      • java.util.Hashtable<String,T>
        • sorcer.core.context.ServiceContext<T>
          • sorcer.core.context.model.par.ParModel<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Remote, Map<String,T>, AssociativeContext<T>, Context<T>, Contexter<T>, Evaluation<T>, Identifiable, Invocation<T>, Mappable<T>, ParModeling, Revaluation

    public class ParModel<T>
extends ServiceContext<T>
implements Evaluation<T>, Invocation<T>, ParModeling
    The ParModel is a shared service context as a map of parameters (Pars), parameter name and its argument is the definition of a independent and dependent arguments. Arguments that dependent on other arguments are subroutines (invokers), so that, each time the subroutine is called, its arguments for that call can be assigned to the corresponding parameters of invokers.
    Author:
    Mike Sobolewski
